SIMPLE: waved
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waved
<hw>Waved</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Exhibiting a
wavelike form or outline; undulating; intended; wavy; <as>as,
<ex>waved</ex> edge</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having a wavelike appearance; marked with wavelike
lines of color; <as>as, <ex>waved</ex>, or watered, silk</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Having undulations like waves; --
said of one of the lines in heraldry which serve as outlines to the
ordinaries, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waveless</ent>⟦br⟧
